Crannian gnome- A race of small, misshapen, dwarf-like creatures that
dwell in the earth. The name 'gnome' was given to them by the medieval scholar 
Paracelcus, in an attempt to describe the most important of the earth spirits. 
Gnomes live under the earth, where they guard treasures. According to Paracelcus
they move as easily through the earth as humans walk upon the ground.
They cannot stand the light of the sun, for even one ray would turn them
to stone. Some sources claim they spend the hours during daylight as a
toad. They are in some way related to goblins and dwarfs.
They have been known to steal neglected human babies to raise as their own.
